Class EventCalendar

java.lang.Object
classes.EventCalendar
public class EventCalendar extends Object
Class that manages an Array of events. Maintains an Event array through add, remove, and print operations.
Author:
Abhishek Thakare, Adhit Thakur

  • Constructor Details

    • EventCalendar

      public EventCalendar(Event[] events, int numEvents)
      Constructor to initialize an EventCalendar.
      Parameters:

  • Method Details

    • find

      private int find(Event event)
      Locate a given Event within the EventCalendar.
      Parameters:
      event - the event to be searched for.
      Returns:
      The index of the event if found, NOT_FOUND otherwise.

    • grow

      private void grow()
      Grow the EventCalendar if max capacity is reached. If the last element in the EventCalendar is non-null, the array needs to grow. Makes 4 more spaces for additional Events.

    • add

      public boolean add(Event event)
      Add an event to the calendar. Checking if valid Event not done here. Simply adding to Calendar.
      Parameters:
      event - The Event to be added.
      Returns:
      true if added to EventCalendar, false otherwise.

    • remove

      public boolean remove(Event event)
      Remove an Event from the EventCalendar. Given an Event, remove that Event entirely from the EventCalendar.
      Parameters:
      event - The Event to be removed.
      Returns:
      true if Event was removed, false otherwise.

    • contains

      public boolean contains(Event event)
      Check if Event is within the EventCalendar.
      Parameters:
      event - The Event to be checked for.
      Returns:
      true if Event is in EventCalendar, false otherwise.

    • print

      public void print()
      Print the EventCalendar unsorted. Based on the order added, print the EventCalendar.

    • printByDate

      public void printByDate()
      Print EventCalendar sorted by Date and Timeslot. First sort by Date then Timeslot within each date. Done using insertion sort in place.

    • printByCampus

      public void printByCampus()
      Print EventCalendar sorted by Campus and Building. First sort by Campus then Building within each Campus. Done using insertion sort in place.

    • printByDepartment

      public void printByDepartment()
      Print EventCalendar sorted by Department. Sort alphabetically by Department. Done using insertion sort in place.

    • getNumEvents

      public int getNumEvents()
      Return the number of events. NOT total capacity.
      Returns:
      number of events currently in EventCalendar.

    • compareTimeslots

      public boolean compareTimeslots(Timeslot one, Timeslot two)
      Compare the Timeslots of two events. Used to sort based on Timeslots, determining which Event is earlier.
      Parameters:
      one - Event that is comparing.
      two - Event that is being compared.
      Returns:
      true if one is earlier than two, false otherwise.
